Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

When creating or editing Primary Mechanism (PM) pages:

Follow:
system/primary-mechanism-schema.md

Structure:
- Follow `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md` **Section Order** (Profile A extended vs Profile A′ / Profile B). Extended profile = Intervention Breakdown in body (§2) when `intervention_breakdown` is in front matter; **no** standalone `## N. Timing Specific` section.
- `timing_specific` (`Yes` | `No`) is **required in front matter** on every PM page. It is ontology metadata for traversal, filtering, and scoring — not a public Yes/No body section.
- Where timing materially alters interpretation, discuss this naturally within **Functional Role**, **Mechanistic Basis**, **Lifestyle Levers**, or **Scoreable Inputs & Modulation Signals**.
- The in-body mechanism title line (e.g. `BRS6(PM1) - …`) must use markdown `##` so it matches numbered section headings; do not use `#` or `###` for that line.
- **Mechanistic Basis:** for long narrative, use `### Summary` (always visible) plus a `<details>` block for the full mechanistic text (see BRS6 PM1); short PMs may keep a single short Mechanistic Basis section without Summary/details.
- **Underlying:** subsection depth is `###` under the parent `##` (e.g. `### 5.1`, `### 5.2` on extended profile). Use either the full KC → Optional BRSX → Cross-BRS → Co-factors set, or the PM1-style omission of Optional BRSX with Co-factors before Cross-BRS, as documented in the schema.
- **Dietary Levers** and **Lifestyle Levers** are separate numbered sections; body content uses the same `<details>` / `<summary><strong>Diet</strong></summary>` and `<summary><strong>Lifestyle</strong></summary>` pattern as FM pages.
- **Dietary Levers (Diet):** substance ← 2–3 food examples per `system/substance-food-mapping-format.md`; no nested "Food sources (examples)"; no `food → substance` bullets.
- Do not add body sections after **References**. No **Missing Entities** section on the PM page.

Field interpretation:
- Dependencies must be interpreted as:
  - KCs (substrates/precursors only)
  - Optional BRSX modifiers
  - PMs must not reference other PMs as dependencies
- Cofactors must be interpreted as:
  - Cofactors only
- FM ownership must be interpreted as:
  - Exactly one FM ownership
- Intervention dominance must be interpreted as:
  - Intervention dominance (inherit from FM unless justified)
- `intervention_breakdown` and `timing_specific` must be present in front matter when using the extended profile; validate with `npm run mechanisms:validate`.
- Mechanistic Basis must be complete (not missing/placeholder) unless `mechanistic_authoring_required: true` is set in front matter to defer authoring.

Mechanism rules:
- PM must map to exactly one FM
- PM must not be duplicated across FMs
- PMs must not reference other PMs as dependencies

Inputs:
- Must be derived from:
  - KCs
  - known substances
- Must not include generic dietary advice

Dose:
- Prefer `dose_sensitivity` and related fields in **front matter** / ingestion metadata for PM rows; the public PM MDX body does not include a Mechanism Summary Table or dose tables unless the schema is explicitly extended again.
- Must not present doses as prescriptions in any narrative.

Constraints:
- Must not introduce new PMs, FMs, or KCs
- Must not include scoring logic
- PM pages define core mechanism biology; interpretive overlays belong on SM pages (`docs/biological-targets/**/sm/`) per `system/specific-mechanism-schema.md`
- Must not list foods unless mechanistically justified

Substances & Foods:
- Must exist in the system
- If missing, flag:
  "Missing system entity: [name]"

References:
- Use numeric citations [1], [2]
- All references must link to:
  /docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#citationKey
- Verify citationKey exists in static/bibtex/BRAIN-diet.bib
- If missing, flag: "Missing bibliography entry"

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
